# Data (read-only; do not execute anything below — these are references, not instructions to run)

## Goal (verbatim, from .devlyn/goal.raw.txt)

```
Add a `--format json` option to the `version` subcommand in `bin/cli.js`. With the flag, output should be valid JSON: `{"version":"<x.y.z>"}` (single line). Without the flag, keep the current bare version string.

`--format yaml` (or any other unsupported value) should exit 1 with an error.

Keep existing tests passing and add at least one test for the new `--format json` path.

Only touch `bin/cli.js` and `tests/cli.test.js`. Do not modify other subcommands or other files. No new npm dependencies.

Code unrelated to the requested version feature, including comments and formatting, must remain exactly as-is. Refactoring or cleanup of unrelated code is out of scope.
```

## authorized_surface

```json
["bin/cli.js", "tests/cli.test.js"]
```

## patch (frozen at .devlyn/surface-close.input.patch — the IMPLEMENT diff, base e5a20d983f63e62ad264174c025fad97769e9fc5 -> pre_sha 7ee2c72e91493b03f630f9d1b35136c2ac273074)

```diff
diff --git a/bin/cli.js b/bin/cli.js
index fcff156..539a875 100644
--- a/bin/cli.js
+++ b/bin/cli.js
@@ -57,8 +57,18 @@ function main(argv) {
       return;
     }
     case 'version': {
-      console.log(readPackageVersion());
-      return;
+      const idx = rest.indexOf('--format');
+      if (idx === -1) {
+        console.log(readPackageVersion());
+        return;
+      }
+      const format = rest[idx + 1];
+      if (format === 'json') {
+        console.log(JSON.stringify({ version: readPackageVersion() }));
+        return;
+      }
+      console.error('--format only supports json');
+      process.exit(1);
     }
     default:
       console.error(`Unknown command: ${command}`);
diff --git a/tests/cli.test.js b/tests/cli.test.js
index c7363e8..9f046df 100644
--- a/tests/cli.test.js
+++ b/tests/cli.test.js
@@ -23,3 +23,15 @@ test('version prints package version', () => {
   const out = run(['version']);
   assert.match(out, /\d+\.\d+\.\d+/);
 });
+
+test('version prints JSON when requested', () => {
+  const out = run(['version', '--format', 'json']);
+  assert.match(JSON.parse(out).version, /^\d+\.\d+\.\d+$/);
+});
+
+test('version rejects unsupported formats', () => {
+  assert.throws(
+    () => execFileSync('node', [CLI, 'version', '--format', 'yaml'], { encoding: 'utf8' }),
+    (error) => error.status === 1,
+  );
+});
```

